                <p><label type="entry">VIGIL</label>, in church history, is the eve or next day
                    before any solemn feast; because then Christians were wont to watch, fast, and
                    pray, in their churches.</p>
                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Vigils</hi>
                    <hi rend="italic">of Plants,</hi> a term under which botanists comprehend the
                    precise time of the day in which the flowers of different plants open, expand,
                    and shut.</p>
            </div>
